<p>After extraction, the yield was calculated using the formula conceptualized by Falleh et al. [
 <xref rid="B59-plants-10-00149" ref-type="bibr">59</xref>]:
 <disp-formula id="FD1-plants-10-00149">
  <math id="mm1">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <mrow>
      <mi mathvariant="normal">R</mi>
      <mtext> </mtext>
     </mrow>
     <mrow>
      <mo>(</mo>
      <mo>%</mo>
      <mo>)</mo>
     </mrow>
     <mtext> </mtext>
     <mo>=</mo>
     <mfrac>
      <mi mathvariant="normal">m</mi>
      <mrow>
       <msub>
        <mi mathvariant="normal">m</mi>
        <mn>0</mn>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
     </mfrac>
     <mo>×</mo>
     <mtext> </mtext>
     <mn>100</mn>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </disp-formula> where R (%) is the yield expressed as a%, m is the mass in grams of the recovered dry extract, and m
 <sub>0</sub> is the mass in grams of the initial plant material.
</p>
